/*!

    \page ai-assistant-ai.html
    \sa {AI assistant},{MCP servers},{Setting up the AI assistant},{Using the AI assistant}
    \title AI models

    The tables below list the models that are available in \QDS by default. To add more models than
    the default ones, see the link to the provider's full list of models below each table.

    The AI assistant supports models from Gemini, OpenAI, and Claude.

    \note The AI assistant in \QDS does not support text-to-speech (TTS).

    \section1 Choosing a model

    When choosing which AI model to use, consider the following:

    \list
      \li You can add more models from the supported providers,
          see \l {Adding, removing, and reorganizing models}.
      \li Access considerations:
        \list
          \li \e Gemini provides
              \l {https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/pricing}{free tier rate limits}, though
              they are limited.
          \li \e OpenAI and \e Claude do not offer any free plans. The pricing depends on the
              model. See \l{https://openai.com/api/pricing/}{OpenAI pricing} and
              \l{https://www.claude.com/pricing#api}{Claude pricing}.
        \endlist
    \endlist

    \section1 Gemini

    \table
      \header
        \li Model
        \li Model ID
        \li Image input
      \row
        \li \l{https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models/gemini-3.1-pro-preview}{Gemini 3.1 Pro Preview}
        \li \c gemini-3.1-pro-preview
        \li Yes
      \row
        \li \l{https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models/gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview}{Gemini 3.1 Flash-Lite Preview}
        \li \c gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview
        \li Yes
      \row
        \li \l{https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models/gemini-3-flash-preview}{Gemini 3 Flash Preview}
        \li \c gemini-3-flash-preview
        \li Yes
      \row
        \li \l{https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models#gemini-2.5-pro}{Gemini 2.5 Pro}
        \li \c gemini-2.5-pro
        \li Yes
      \row
        \li \l{https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models#gemini-2.5-flash}{Gemini 2.5 Flash}
        \li \c gemini-2.5-flash
        \li Yes
      \row
        \li \l{https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models#gemini-2.5-flash-lite}{Gemini 2.5 Flash-Lite}
        \li \c gemini-2.5-flash-lite
